<DOC><DOCNO> AP890305-0007 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-03-05-89 1141EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Nigeria     03-05 0160</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Nigeria,0166</SECOND><HEAD>Four Killed In Riot Caused By Hit-and-Run Accident</HEAD><DATELINE>LAGOS, Nigeria (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A hit-and-run bus accident touched off aclash between police and people armed with broken bottles andstones, and four people were shot to death and five injured,authorities said Sunday.   Police said the riot occurred Friday night when a bus drivertrying to escape a traffic policeman ran down and killed a commuter.   Youths in the area of central Lagos began attacking police andgovernment vehicles, injuring five policemen, one of themcritically, police said.   Riot police sent to the scene were greeted by rocks and bottlesthrown from behind a barracade erected by the rioters, police said.   Authorities fired tear gas and pistols to break up the riot.Police said four people died from bullet wounds.   Last month a policeman was sentenced to death for killing two meninvolved in a traffic dispute. That traffic accident caused riotsthat left eight people dead.</TEXT></DOC>